properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 29 at 3:37AM AKST until March 2 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Fairbanks AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow expected. Plan on slippery road
conditions. In addition, areas of poor visibility are expected.
Tree branches could fall as well. South of Black Rapids, total
snow accumulations of 4 to 6 inches,are expected. South winds
gusting as high as 60 mph in passes.

* WHERE...Eastern Alaska Range.

* WHEN...6 PM today to 6 AM Monday.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Winds gusting as high as 60 mph will cause
areas of blowing and drifting snow. Visibility may be reduced to
one half mile or less at times. Strongest winds expected to
develop this evening and continue overnight before diminishing
Sunday morning.
properties.instruction:
A Winter Weather Advisory for snow and blowing snow means periods
of snow and blowing snow will cause travel difficulties. The
latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM AKST MONDAY
